  m_Name: 36_Simulation
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  chapter: 9
  number: 36
  title: Buoyancy Simulation
  description: "This simulation demonstrates how density and volume affect an object\u2019s
    ability to float or sink in a fluid. By adjusting the sliders, you can observe
    how changes in these properties influence buoyant force and equilibrium."
  objectives: "To understand the relationship between density, volume, and buoyancy.\n\nTo
    observe how an object\u2019s density compared to water determines if it floats,
    sinks, or stays suspended.\n\nTo develop prediction skills about buoyant behavior
    through interactive adjustment."
  scoring: 
  bronzeObjective: 
  silverObjective: 
  goldObjective: 
  timeBonus:
    timeBonuses: []
    lowestScore: 10
  unlockDatas:
  - icon: 3
    name: Level 37 - Challenge
    description: Underwater Mining
  - icon: 2
    name: Freeplay > Simulation 9
    description: Buoyancy Simulation
  instructions: "1. Observe the box submerged in the fluid.\n\n2. Use the Density
    and Volume sliders to adjust the object\u2019s physical properties.\n\n3. Aim
    to achieve equilibrium where the object neither sinks completely nor floats out
    of the water.\n\n4. Press End Simulation when done.\n\nNote: If the box is touched
    or adjustments are made, a 5-second countdown begins before auto win (successful
    stabilization). If no adjustments are made within 15 seconds, the simulation
    ends automatically."
